    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">McKenzie</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 146.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Neill’s No. 243, of September 13
                    last, in regard to the claim of the Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon, I
                    have to inquire whether the Government of Peru has taken any action in regard to
                    this claim, the justice of which has been so often admitted.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
